  "The Moon was thought to be completely dry — water on the surface challenged decades of understanding": "",
  "We always knew there was water there": "",
  "India was the first country to the Moon": "",
  "Water is common on all moons": "",
  "Before Chandrayaan and other missions confirmed it, the Moon was believed to be anhydrous (completely waterless).": "",
  "SpaceX's Starship is being developed for Mars missions. What makes the reusable design important for Mars exploration?": "",
  "Reusable rocket designs achieve significantly higher exhaust velocities and thrust-to-weight ratios than expendable launch vehicles of comparable size": "",
  "Reusability dramatically reduces launch costs, making frequent Mars missions economically feasible": "",
  "Federal space agency regulations mandate that all launch vehicles used for interplanetary missions must incorporate fully reusable first-stage booster designs": "",
  "The iterative testing and reflight of reusable rocket hardware produces statistically lower failure rates than single-use expendable launch vehicle systems": "",
  "Reuse reduces per-launch cost by orders of magnitude, essential for the many launches needed to transport humans and cargo to Mars.": ""
